1297,IssuesEvent,2015-10-11 14:24:53+00:00,31262911,jaraco/keyring,308610,jaraco,,,closed,pyfs keyring fails horribly on pyfs 0.5.,[],[],1,"pyfs has released a new, backward-incompatible version that adds Python 3 support. Unfortunately, this new version has serious problems with keyring, probably rooted in fundamental problems in configparser.

Because configparser writes native 'str' objects to the stream (e.g. `fp.write(""\n"")`), those calls fail on Python 2 if the file is opened in text mode and fail on Python 3 if the file was opened in binary mode (because fs is strict about the input type even on Python 2).

I won't be able to solve this issue, so I'm going to mark the tests as xfail and hope a volunteer can help resolve the issues. If they're not resolved, I'll consider pulling support for pyfs.

----------------------------------------
- Bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/kang/python-keyring-lib/issue/156
- Originally reported by: Jason R. Coombs
- Originally created at: 2015-01-26T23:29:51.139
",{},{}
1299,IssuesEvent,2015-02-23 21:35:07+00:00,31230734,jaraco/keyring,308610,jaraco,,,opened,cannot use python-keyring and python-crypto together any more,[],[],2,"Hi,

Until now under GNU/Linux Debian Wheezy when I tried to use python keyring 0.7.1  with python-crypto everything was fine. But trying to upgrade to 0.8.1 I had the following issue while executing the example auth_demo.py:

    
    
    sid2:/usr/share/doc/python-keyring/examples# python auth_demo.py 
    Username:
    john
    Password:
    
    Password file found in legacy location
      /root/crypted_pass.cfg
    and new location
      /root/.local/share/python_keyring/crypted_pass.cfg
    Old location will be ignored.
    Please input your password for the keyring
    Wrong password for the keyring.
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File ""auth_demo.py"", line 56, in <module>
        main()
      File ""auth_demo.py"", line 50, in main
        keyring.set_password('auth_demo_login', username, password)
      File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/keyring/core.py"", line 42, in set_password
        _keyring_backend.set_password(service_name, username, password)
      File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/keyring/backend.py"", line 328, in set_password
        password_encrypted = self.encrypt(password.encode('utf-8'))
      File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/keyring/backend.py"", line 471, in encrypt
        crypter = self._init_crypter()
      File ""/usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/keyring/backend.py"", line 459, in _init_crypter
        raise ValueError(""Wrong password"")
    ValueError: Wrong password
    

It keeps telling me the message above even if I delete auth_demo.cfg just before.

If I remove python-crypto, everything is back to normal:
    
    Username:
    carl
    Password:
    
    Authorization successful.
    sid2:/usr/share/doc/python-keyring/examples# python auth_demo.py 
    Authorization successful.
    
In python-keyring 0.7.1 it was working with python-crypto very well.
Bye,
Carl Chenet


  

