2746,IssuesEvent,2018-06-18 23:05:15+00:00,85603555,molpopgen/fwdpy11,6416159,molpopgen,,,opened,Potential cppimport issue with new Anaconda compilers,[],[],0,"When testing out the [new compilers](https://conda.io/docs/user-guide/tasks/build-packages/compiler-tools.html) in a clean env on Linux, the main package built fine but the unit tests did not.  They could not find GSL headers.  While this clearly seems like a compiler config issue, the following can be added to the mako headers to make sure that GSL's headers are found:

```py
import subprocess
GSL=subprocess.run(['gsl-config','--cflags'],stdout=subprocess.PIPE).stdout.strip(b'-I').decode().strip()
cfg['include_dirs'].extend([GSL, fp11.get_includes(), fp11.get_fwdpp_includes() ])
```

Curiously, the unit tests executed, suggesting no run-time linker issues.",{},{}
