2776,IssuesEvent,2016-11-10 08:50:54+00:00,2909429,nicolargo/glances,776747,nicolargo,,,closed,PID column too small if kernel.pid_max is > 99999,"[{'id': 204819, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nicolargo/glances/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '207de5', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'nicolargo', 'id': 776747, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/776747?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nicolargo', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nicolargo/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"I run several systems with kernel.pid_max set to 4194303.

With this setting a PID column of only 6 characters (5 for the numbers and 1 for the spacing) is too small and causes the display to look ugly.

A quick fix would be to increase the size from 6 to 8, but this would waste space on systems with the normal pid_max setting. 

The optimal way would be to read kernel.pid_max and adjust automatically.",{},{}
