3590,IssuesEvent,2018-03-23 00:07:55+00:00,69090889,hardbyte/python-can,4403130,felixdivo,,,closed,Stay alive while there is work to do,"[{'id': 448741911, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/hardbyte/python-can/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 448749073, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/hardbyte/python-can/labels/major', 'name': 'major', 'color': 'ededed', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Originally reported by: **Brian Thorne (Bitbucket: [hardbyte](https://bitbucket.org/hardbyte), GitHub: [hardbyte](https://github.com/hardbyte))**

---

The transmit threads don't prevent the Python interpreter from shutting down - which if they have out bound messages in their queue means messages won't get transmitted.

A simple but horrible solution is to wait or sleep after sending in a short program. A better solution would be great.

---
- Bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/hardbyte/python-can/issue/3
",{},{}
