3689,IssuesEvent,2017-09-27 06:16:22+00:00,67834502,lk-geimfari/mimesis,15812620,lk-geimfari,,,closed,Refactoring gender() method so it returns an Enum.,"[{'id': 439881093, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/lk-geimfari/mimesis/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 697428661, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/lk-geimfari/mimesis/labels/Hacktoberfest', 'name': 'Hacktoberfest', 'color': 'FFB61E', 'default': False}, {'id': 439881094, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/lk-geimfari/mimesis/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '128A0C', 'default': True}]",[],0,"At this moment, methods related to gender return the default values for `female`. It is necessary that the floor is selected randomly.

@wikkiewikkie  suggested using the following format (in this [issue](https://github.com/lk-geimfari/mimesis/pull/155#issuecomment-288398995)) :

```python
>>> my_gender = personal.gender()

>>> type(my_gender)
<enum 'Gender'>

>>> my_gender
female

>>> my_gender.iso5218()
2

>>> my_gender.symbol()
♀

>>> first_name = personal.first_name(gender=my_gender)
>>> first_name
