7366,IssuesEvent,2018-02-18 10:42:00+00:00,6930489,facebook/watchman,1144727,frankie567,69631,facebook,opened,Can't talk to socket which name contains UTF-8 characters in Windows,[],[],0,"Hi,

I'm trying to use watchman on Windows. My Windows username is **François** (notice the cedilla). By default, watchman will create a socket based on this username. As we can see in the ProcessExplorer screenshot below, it can create it:

![processexplorer](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1144727/36350849-8e7b1afc-149f-11e8-87d8-49d4b62c4c62.png)

Unfortunately, when trying to issue command to the server, it can't communicate with the socket (`[cli] unable to talk to your watchman on \\.\pipe\watchman-Franþois! (No error)`):

![clierror](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1144727/36350869-e9b4f6ae-149f-11e8-984e-50baa150eb4c.png)

I tried on the same computer with an account containing only ASCII characters, and it works like a charm ; that's why I suspect an issue with UTF-8 characters.

I use the latest Windows build proposed on appveyor ([b1480](https://ci.appveyor.com/project/wez/watchman/build/b1480)).
",{},{}
