We can see that `2018-06-04 21:06:11,536:DEBUG:impala.hiveserver2:Transport opened` is generated after a successful LDAP bind on the Impala side:

```
I0604 21:06:11.527957 6251 authentication.cc:249] Trying simple LDAP bind for: uid=abannin,cn=users,cn=compat,dc=dc,dc=internal 
I0604 21:06:11.534382 6251 authentication.cc:261] LDAP bind successful 
I0604 21:06:11.534394 6251 authentication.cc:459] Successfully authenticated client user ""abannin""
```

I made a quick script to verify connection with just sqlalchemy (no Superset), and it fails the same way:

```
import sqlalchemy

print('begin')
engine = sqlalchemy.create_engine('impala://{host}:21050/default?auth_mechanism=PLAIN&password={password}&user={user}')
print('created engine {}'.format(engine))

conn = engine.connect()
print('connected conn={} closed={} info={}'.format(conn, conn.closed, conn.info))

res = conn.execute(""show tables"")
print(res.fetchall())
print('fin')
```

Any thoughts on causes or possible remedies?",{},{}
