8140,IssuesEvent,2016-06-09 21:49:37+00:00,6670942,boto/botocore,2643092,JordonPhillips,327752,boto,closed,Feature request:  Add ability to ignore params in stubber,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/boto/botocore/labels/feature-request', 'name': 'feature-request', 'color': 'fbca04'}]",[],0,"It would be nice if the stubber had a solution for being able to ignore randomly generated values in the input.  For example:

* idempotency tokens
* statement ids

And really anything that typically is a random value.  

There's a few ways I can think of to accomplish this.  In `mock`, you can use `mock.ANY` to indicate that you don't care about the value.   In the CLI we have an `ignore_params` for `assert_params_for_cmd`, though this only works for top level params (which typically is sufficient).",{},{}
