What I'm trying to do with RF is to remotely ssh to a server via a ssh proxy server using public/private key. 

machine-c ------------> machine-p ------------> machine-t
 (ssh client) (ssh proxy) (target server)

From a ssh client machine-c, a ssh connection is first made to a ssh proxy machine-p then additional ssh connection to a target server machine-t. The ssh proxy is defined in ~/.ssh/config as below in client machine-c;

Host machine-p
 Hostname 10.10.10.10

Host machine-t.example.com
 ProxyCommand ssh machine-p nc machine-t.example.com

On Linux CLI, giving ""ssh machine-t.example.com"" takes me into machine-t successfully without asking password. And the log message in /var/log/secure at machine-t.example.com shows that a ssh connection came from ssh proxy machine-p.

