8827,IssuesEvent,2018-07-19 09:05:14+00:00,27086567,scrapinghub/dateparser,7307772,alvaroabascar,699596,scrapinghub,opened,"Inconsistency in the parser behaviour with and without date_formats, with respect to using first/last day of month.",[],[],0,"This is the expected defautl behaviour of `dateparser.parser`. If we do not specify the day in the date, we get the same day of the month as today (I'm writting as of July 19th 2018).

```python3
dateparser.parse('august 2016')
# >> datetime.datetime(2016, 8, 19, 0, 0)
```
Now let's say we want to parse ""august-16"" as ""august of 2016"", so we use the custom format `""%B-%y""`. We obtain the following result:
```python3
dateparser.parse('august-16', date_formats=['%B-%y'])
# >> datetime.datetime(2016, 8, 31, 0, 0)
```

In this case, instead of obtaining the same result as before, we got the last day of august (31). Unless I'm missing something, I believe the result should be the same in both cases.",{},{}
