9082,IssuesEvent,2015-03-20 19:17:28+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,2096628,blink1073,897180,scikit-image,reopened,converting dtype in ImageCollection,[],[],3,"I am just getting into scikit image and came across some weird issue. I want to load a bunch of images as an ImageCollection, which works just fine. However, all images are loaded as uint8, but I need to have all images in the collection to be uint16.

When I try to use the example code from http://scikit-image.org/docs/dev/api/skimage.io.html#skimage.io.ImageCollection:
```python
def imread_convert(f):
    return imread(f).astype(np.uint8)

ic = ImageCollection('/tmp/*.png', load_func=imread_convert)
```
I get an error when trying to use the collection as normal, for example plot the data:
```
imread_convert() got an unexpected keyword argument 'img_num'
```
How is it possible to convert all images to another dtype? I tried simply mapping the utility-function and it works:
```python
ic = list(map(img_as_uint, ic))
```
Now I want to build a super class over ImageCollection and this solution is not applicable because (as far as I know) I would reassign `self`. I can't find the attribute where the data is stored, trying to
```python
self.data = list(map(img_as_uint, self.data))
```
yields to 
```
can not convert object to uint16
```
Sorry if this is a stupid question, I am shure I am missing something.",{},{}
9083,IssuesEvent,2015-12-09 19:05:17+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,45071,stefanv,897180,scikit-image,opened,regionprops: document each property for introspection purposes,[],[],0,,{},{}
9090,IssuesEvent,2018-06-27 18:39:34+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,90008,hmaarrfk,897180,scikit-image,opened,Failures in --pre builds,[],[],0,"This first showed up in the windows builds failing.
this was due to to the fact that the --pre flag was enabled by default.

PR #3222 attempts to make this more obvious by dedicating a --pre build to the build matrix.

I have a hunch it is due to numpy 1.15.rc1

On travis this wasn't showing up for some reason. I triggered a build on my fork of master (updated) and the dedicated --pre build fails to pull in the numpy 1.15.rc1 dependency from upstream https://travis-ci.org/hmaarrfk/scikit-image/jobs/397451046#L861

When this PR builds, #3227, travis will pull in prereleases from pypi too the problem should show up for travis too.
I've found that while the --pre build compiles with numpy 1.15.rc1, it fails some tests on linux.

",{},{}
