9115,IssuesEvent,2018-04-29 05:50:38+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,1315589,soupault,897180,scikit-image,closed,Image Inversion for signed types,"[{'id': 360216647, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/labels/status:%20needs%20decision', 'name': 'status: needs decision', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}]",[],8,"## Description
Image inversion for signed types does not yield the expected result. 

`In [7]: img = np.array([[0, 1, -125], [1, 0, 125]], dtype=np.int8)`

`In [8]: invert(img)`
`Out[8]: `
`array([[127, 126,  -4],
       [126, 127,   2]], dtype=int8)`

I guess, that image inversion should do different things depending on the data type. If the data type is signed, inversion should more or less multiply with (-1) (with the problem that the range is not symmetric). 


