9123,IssuesEvent,2018-08-26 08:50:10+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,36897778,abTest-123,897180,scikit-image,opened,optimization of Find file  Copy path  scikit-image/skimage/feature/_texture.pyx ,[],[],0,"## Description
When calculating GLCM using the _glcm_loop, the offset pixel calculation can be optimized slightly.
In lines 68-69 the pixel offset value is calculated per each element, those offset values are constant and require both the calculation of a trigonometric function and casting to a different variable type.
By calculating the rowOffset and columnOffset ouside of the loop those executions need only happen once.
                        row = r + <int>round(sin(angle) * distance)
                        col = c + <int>round(cos(angle) * distance)

Some further optimization can be done by using the offset size(s) to reduce the number of iterations by changing the range of the for loops in lines 63 and 64.
In my opinion it would be wiser to change the convention from distance and angle to  rowOffset and columnOffset, but that does not conform with the standard notations.



",{},{}
9169,IssuesEvent,2017-11-07 14:33:23+00:00,33125412,5monkeys/django-bananas,137268,lundberg,1019061,5monkeys,closed,ExtendedQuerySet doesn't return all possible combinations when renaming reverse relation fields,[],[],0,"This only affects the Django1.9+ version of `ExtendedQuerySet`.

Using the Parent/Child models used in the tests as an example:

```
>>> p = Parent.objects.create(name=""P"")
>>> c1 = Child.objects.create(parent=p, name=""C1"")
>>> c2 = Child.objects.create(parent=p, name=""C2"")

>>> Parent.objects.filter(name=""P"").dicts(child_name=""child__name"")
[{'child_name': 'C1'}, {}]

>>> # It only affects renamed fields
>>> Parent.objects.filter(name=""P"").dicts(""child__name"")
[{'child__name': 'C1'}, {'child__name': 'C2'}]
```

Attempted fix #10 

",{},{}
