9242,IssuesEvent,2017-03-02 17:26:35+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,1441066,vitaly-krugl,1039191,numenta,closed,"When built with -DGLIBCXX_DEBUG, c++ detects out-of-bounds access to _synapses in Segment::freeNSynapses","[{'id': 119506192, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/priority:2', 'name': 'priority:2', 'color': 'eb6420', 'default': False}, {'id': 378140281, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/triage', 'name': 'triage', 'color': 'AAAAAA', 'default': False}, {'id': 78895566, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/numenta/nupic.core/labels/type:build', 'name': 'type:build', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'vitaly-krugl', 'id': 1441066, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1441066?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/vitaly-krugl', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/vitaly-krugl/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",8,"Build nupic.core with -DGLIBCXX_DEBUG, and install nupic.bindings from that build. Then install matching nupic and run the tests `python nupic/tests/unit/nupic/research/tp10x2_test.py --verbose`. More specifically, you may run `python tp10x2_test.py TPTest.testCheckpointMiddleOfSequence2` to get directly to the offending test.

The debug build of C++ containers detects access to element 30 (0-based) in a 30-element container `_synapses` in `nupic::algorithms::Cells4::Segment::freeNSynapses`

The C++ container emits the following messages before aborting the test:

```
/opt/rh/devtoolset-2/root/usr/include/c++/4.8.2/debug/vector:346:error: 
    attempt to subscript container with out-of-bounds index 30, but 
    container only holds 30 elements.

Objects involved in the operation:
sequence ""this"" @ 0x0x46ecbf0 {
  type = NSt7__debug6vectorIN5nupic10algorithms6Cells49InSynapseESaIS4_EEE;
}
```

Here is the section of the offending code from https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/bdc7d890497af242e68b5344dff1e21ca799cc46/src/nupic/algorithms/Segment.cpp#L371-L377:

```
  // We first choose from inactive synapses, in order of increasing permanence
  InSynapses candidates;
  for (UInt i = 0; i < inactiveSegmentIndices.size(); i++)
  {
    // Put in *segment indices*, not source cell indices
    candidates.push_back(InSynapse(inactiveSegmentIndices[i],
      _synapses[inactiveSegmentIndices[i]].permanence()));
  }
```

