9244,IssuesEvent,2016-03-05 02:46:00+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,239726,scottpurdy,1039191,numenta,closed,"Having multiple ""Scalar.cpp"" files causes link errors. Switch to ""ScalarEncoder.cpp""",[],[],0,"I'll fix this in an upcoming change. I just wanted to vent into a Github issue first.

I put the ScalarEncoder in `nupic/encoders/Scalar.cpp`, matching the Python `encoders` folder. But during a build, there are two files being compiled to `Scalar.cpp.o`, and `nupic/ntypes/Scalar.cpp` wins the fight. It does all this quietly, and then you get a mysterious link error later.",{},{}
