9372,IssuesEvent,2015-04-04 13:48:29+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,633680,jalavik,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,BibClassify: performance issues and false results,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_BibClassify', 'name': 'c_BibClassify', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/master', 'name': 'master', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/s_INSPIRE', 'name': 's_INSPIRE', 'color': '207de5'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_bug', 'name': 't_bug', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],0,"We noticed that BibClassify often got ""stuck"", e.g. taking an unreasonable long time, on our labs instance. In addition some keywords extracted were plain wrong. Local testing did not reveal the same behavior. After some debugging it turned out that:

* `is_pdf()` check do not correctly work with PDFs having colons in the filename when extracting the fulltext - causing bad data to be passed onwards and cause wrong results and the performance issues.
* After extracting the text from a PDF references are removed, but it is not always working well. E.g. removes the entire fulltext if first page has a table of contents mentioning *References*.

A PR is incoming that addresses these issues by using refextract api that already does this job better and initial testing shows that things are working way better.",{},{}
9373,IssuesEvent,2015-09-13 17:23:28+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,189798,jirikuncar,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,accounts: user creation with id = 1 problem on PostgreSQL,[],[],0,"PostgreSQL doesn't update the sequence after insertion of [users fixtures](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio/blob/master/invenio/modules/accounts/fixtures.py#L32) (user admin).

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/9108833/postgres-autoincrement-not-updated-on-explicit-id-inserts

Here you can read that:

> That's how it's supposed to work - next_val('test_id_seq') is only called when the system needs a value for this column and you have not provided one. If you provide value no such call is performed and consequently the sequence is not ""updated"".

So, after inserting the user admin in the table, the sequence associated with the id is not updated.
It means that next user that will be inserted will generate the error:

```python
IntegrityError: (psycopg2.IntegrityError) duplicate key value violates unique constraint ""user_pkey""
DETAIL:  Key (id)=(1) already exists.
```

A possible solution is to not specify the id in `fixtures.py`.
Any ideas? :)",{},{}
