9567,IssuesEvent,2015-11-27 13:14:48+00:00,36870897,ska-sa/spead2,1963944,bmerry,1210238,ska-sa,closed,Race condition causes use-after-free when sending,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ska-sa/spead2/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ska-sa/spead2/labels/c++', 'name': 'c++', 'color': 'bfdadc'}]",[],0,"spead2::send::stream::send_next_packet allocates the next packet on the stack, then asynchronously sends it. This means that the memory dynamically allocated for holding the header and item pointers can be freed before they are transmitted if the socket would block.",{},{}
9599,IssuesEvent,2015-02-22 01:23:03+00:00,15958352,GetBlimp/django-rest-framework-jwt,83319,jpadilla,1227237,GetBlimp,closed,Notes on  RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 Should be Updates,[],[],1,">For the RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 algorithms, the ""secret"" argument in jwt.encode is supposed to be a private RSA key as imported with Crypto.PublicKey.RSA.importKey. Likewise, the ""secret"" argument in jwt.decode is supposed to be the public RSA key imported with the same method.

1. It isn't clear what library has `Crypto.PublicKey.RSA.importKey`
2. Probably want to use `cryptography` anyways
3. `pyjwt` handles strings now in some cases so no special action is needed,",{},{}
