9646,IssuesEvent,2018-05-13 16:36:34+00:00,2866041,kivy/python-for-android,33596368,move[bot],1266152,kivy,opened,App crash when connecting to mysql,[],[],0,"*@Mark-Wellings commented on Feb 24, 2018, 10:53 AM UTC:*

### Versions

*   Python: 3.6
*   OS: Windows 10
*   Kivy: 1.10.0
*   Kivy installation method: pip

### Description

Dear all,

My main.py is working fine, when running it with python 3.6 locally on Windows. I can log on and sign up to a mysql db located on server hosted on digitalocean.

When I deploy it via the VM I can still open the application and switch between screens, but when I try to connect to the mysql database on a server the application crashes.
With adb logcat *W: I get the following log: [logcat Warnings .txt](https://github.com/kivy/kivy/files/1754283/logcat.Warnings.txt)
I think the problem is the following:

> /lib/arm/libpython2.7.so (PyThreadState_New+93)

> /lib/arm/libpython2.7.so (PyThreadState_New+93)

I've uploaded the project to my github under: [https://github.com/Mark-Wellings/mykivy](url)

Where you'll find the main.py, main.kv, buildozer spec and the logcat.txt.

Thanks for your help.

*This issue was moved by [tshirtman](https://github.com/tshirtman) from kivy/kivy/issues/5633.*",{},{}
