10039,IssuesEvent,2016-02-23 19:35:29+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,623887,rmjarvis,1462196,GalSim-developers,opened,Unsigned int Images,[],[],0,"On branch #654, I fixed a number of problems that we had related to reading in unsigned int Images.  We don't have any unsigned int instantiations for the Image class in C++, so it had been recognizing the incompatibility and converting to float64 (our default catchall if we can't handle the dtype of a numpy array).  

However, for badpix masks, this isn't the right thing to do, so now the code uses the corresponding int type instead.  i.e. uint16 -> int16 and uint32 -> int32.  This works ok, but it would be better if we actually supported uint Images correctly.",{},{}
