10578,IssuesEvent,2017-06-29 11:10:27+00:00,15510254,openfisca/openfisca-core,222463,MattiSG,1794404,openfisca,opened,Remove scenarios,"[{'id': 309665896, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openfisca/openfisca-core/labels/developer-experience', 'name': 'developer-experience', 'color': 'eb6420', 'default': False}, {'id': 72578811, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openfisca/openfisca-core/labels/needs-consensus', 'name': 'needs-consensus', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': False}, {'id': 550567915, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openfisca/openfisca-core/labels/vocabulary', 'name': 'vocabulary', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],0,"They are poorly named, as they do three things:

1. Input validation through entities consistency checks.
2. Relationships completion between entities.
3. Parse the situation Python instance from an input.

## Consensus

- Refactor by renaming & splitting roles.

## Uncertainties

- Should we keep input validation? This is in the law, but is not consistently handled by OpenFisca.
- Should we replace relationships completion by situation templates?",{},{}
