10690,IssuesEvent,2018-08-27 08:42:03+00:00,37136408,algolia/algoliasearch-django,123822,vvo,2034458,algolia,opened,"When reindexing, the _tmp suffix can cause issues with index restricted keys","[{'id': 860625893, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw4NjA2MjU4OTM=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/algoliasearch-django/labels/Enhancement', 'name': 'Enhancement', 'color': '3369e6', 'default': False}]",[],0,"When reindexing, the code adds _tmp to the constructed index name:
https://github.com/algolia/algoliasearch-django/blob/ce9447c6a45749f55b48f27bb1c4d58710ce480a/algoliasearch_django/models.py#L163-L173

Some users are using dedicated environment keys where there's an index restriction like ""only for indexes named *_dev"". Which mean that on reindexing the key won't be able to reindex because of the way we constructed the tmp index name.

Since we have very descriptive settings, I guess we could do something like this:

```txt
if prefix => tmp_index_name = index_name + tmp + env
if suffix => tmp_index_name = env + tmp + index_name
```

This should be sufficient?",{},{}
