11369,IssuesEvent,2018-07-13 17:40:40+00:00,28885080,cloudtools/stacker,517334,phobologic,3028687,cloudtools,closed,MissingEnvironment sometimes isn't raised,"[{'id': 163635462, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWwxNjM2MzU0NjI=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/cloudtools/stacker/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],2,"We noticed this happen internally, where a key that was specified in remind.yaml, was missing in the env file, but stacker never raised `MissingEnvironment`. The reason it never gets raised, is because when we call [t.substitute](https://github.com/remind101/stacker/blob/e7e0e02575bbbc162249af7ceb2418f50b9b06d2/stacker/config/__init__.py#L84), if the `strings.Template` parser first hits a lookup (e.g. `${kms ...}`), then it'll raise a ValueError and fallback to calling [t.safe_substitute](https://github.com/remind101/stacker/blob/e7e0e02575bbbc162249af7ceb2418f50b9b06d2/stacker/config/__init__.py#L89), which will never raised an exception if there's a missing key in the env.

Here's a test that demonstrates the bug: https://github.com/remind101/stacker/commit/5e83ffb2de7fa38dae1ee9b5dae9f6c7b7767333

/cc @russellballestrini @phobologic ",{},{}
