11447,IssuesEvent,2015-11-12 07:30:46+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,Pants should ship with a python requirement pointing to itself.,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"Best explained by a custom plugin build file alias I just wrote for Aurora:
```python
def build_file_aliases():
  # This should ship as part of pants core - any custom plugin writer will want to have their
  # plugin depend on the same version of pants as the one their running.  
  pants_requirement = PythonRequirement('pantsbuild.pants==%s' % pants_version())
  return BuildFileAliases(objects={'pants_requirement': pants_requirement})
```",{},{}
