11518,IssuesEvent,2015-08-17 16:59:00+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,GoTest does not trigger resolution of .TestImports,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/Medium', 'name': 'Medium', 'color': '6F4E37'}]",[],0,"This leads to the test binary failing to compile.

Right now GoTest and GoCompile both depend on GoFetch via their GoWorkspace superclass, but they have no way to communicate their dep resolution needs since there is no go_tests target.  Introducing these targets would be one way to solve the problem, fetching both .Imports and .TestImports and classifying these under different products would be another.",{},{}
