11590,IssuesEvent,2017-12-28 17:01:03+00:00,105830539,awslabs/mxnet-model-server,11851621,treske,3299148,awslabs,opened,Cannot start mxnet-model-server on non-default port.,[],[],0,"Using the --port option for mxnet-model-server fails with the following error:
Failed to start model serving host: Flask handler failed to start: port must be an integer

Steps to recreate:

```bash
mkdir -p ~/env/mxnet-model-server-port-issue 
python3 -m venv ~/env/mxnet-model-server-port-issue
source ~/env/mxnet-model-server-port-issue/bin/activate
pip install mxnet-model-server    
cd ~/env/mxnet-model-server-port-issue
mxnet-model-server --models squeezenet=https://s3.amazonaws.com/model-server/models/squeezenet_v1.1/squeezenet_v1.1.model --log-file ~/env/mxnet-model-server-port-issue/mms.log --log-level DEBUG --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8090
```

One way to fix would be to change line 135 in mms/mxnet_model_server.py

from
self.port = self.args.port or 8080
to
self.port = int(self.args.port) or 8080
",{},{}
