When downloading builds from `buildkite/kolibri/assets` details link, filenames are too complex and difficult to distinguish. 

![selection_655](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1457929/31338580-259d1370-ad00-11e7-9c8a-f890d2515631.png)

These links do save some time, but filenames are longer then those downloaded individually from Buildkite (green). Could we make them shorter? For example, get rid of the useless prefix and various `%2F` in between in order to make this:

`kolibri%2Fbuildkite%2Fbuild-2313%2F2755%2Fkolibri-0.6.dev020170929214748-git.pex` (red)

into this:

`build-2313-kolibri-0.6.dev020170929214748-git.pex` (yellow)

Or just `kolibri-0.6.dev020170929214748-git.pex` if those build details are not necessary.

![selection_653](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1457929/31339729-198fddf2-ad04-11e7-8b85-d1e0125600e4.png)",{},{}
