11862,IssuesEvent,2017-10-27 02:31:25+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,2367265,indirectlylit,3926525,learningequality,closed,<Tabs> component currently hides some items on mobile,[],"[{'login': 'christianmemije', 'id': 7193975, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/7193975?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/christianmemije', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/christianmemije/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",11,"# Summary

Currently, narrow displays obscure items on the <Tabs> Component. This has been pointed out by @laurenlichtman, @jamalex, and UNICEF.

Currently, overflow allows scroll, which isn't ideal. Apart from that, the affordance isn't clear - the scroll bar is invisible on most mobile devices.

@laurenlichtman made mentions of an indicator to show that there's more to see. Maybe even a button that would scroll the nav.


## Screenshots (Photocreds to @laurenlichtman) 

![starting to scroll](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9877852/28682666-969a46d4-72b2-11e7-8107-9e00a98bc3f0.png)
![still and unclear that there are more items](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9877852/28682675-9d23c91c-72b2-11e7-9580-a77e273302d3.png)
![landscape](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9877852/28682676-a433aa38-72b2-11e7-837a-65d3afc51166.png)



## Real-life consequences (anything community should be aware of, for instance how it affects your deployment)

Users don't know all the options available to them in management, and other potentially long subnavs",{},{}
