11887,IssuesEvent,2018-05-19 00:02:32+00:00,66887069,learningequality/ricecooker,163966,ivanistheone,3926525,learningequality,closed,Mandatory 'nomonitor' breaks souschef,[],[],2,"* ricecooker version: 0.6.16 (was fine in .13, I think)
* Python version: 3.5.2
* Operating System: Ubuntu 16.04

### Description

I tried to run an existing souschef (https://github.com/learningequality/sushi-chef-artsedge) and after upgrading it gave a KeyError for 'nomonitor' on https://github.com/learningequality/ricecooker/blob/f75986ac2681b64dee74697eb2863c4db05cb30c/ricecooker/commands.py#L110

This leads to calling `.run` on a `SushiChef` instance to crash if no `nomonitor` attribute is provided.

### What I Did

I can work around this by adding `nomonitor=False` to the invocation -- this isn't ideal since every souschef file will need to be updated.

I recommend we change `kwargs['nomonitor']` to `kwargs.get('nomonitor')` which will return None (assuming that's acceptable behavior) or explicitly set a default value with `kwargs.get('nomonitor', True)` or similarly for False.

@ivanistheone -- pinging since you'll probably have the best idea what the default should be.
",{},{}
11900,IssuesEvent,2018-07-25 05:48:25+00:00,12426527,crate/crate-python,48020,dobe,4048232,crate,opened,Client should gracefully handle connection resets,[],[],0,"When a server due to inactivity closes its connection, a socket error is raised when the client tries to use the connection - this is expected behaviour, however the crate client removes the given server from its active server lists as if it was down, which is wrong. This leads to no remaining servers exceptions if only one server is used in the connection. In conjunction with #302 this leads to sporadic exceptions which could be handled gracefully on the http level. 

example traceback:

```
Traceback (most recent call last):
File ""/usr/local/lib/python3.6/site-packages/sqlalchemy/engine/base.py"", line 1193, in _execute_context
data_sent += socket.send(chunk, flags)
File ""/usr/local/lib/python3.6/site-packages/gevent/_socket3.py"", line 440, in send
return _socket.socket.send(self._sock, data, flags)
urllib3.exceptions.ProtocolError: ('Connection aborted.', ConnectionResetError(104, 'Connection reset by peer'))
```


",{},{}
