12006,IssuesEvent,2017-05-31 17:51:39+00:00,53143022,oduwsdl/ipwb,2514780,machawk1,4416806,oduwsdl,closed,Sample indexes are outdated,"[{'id': 336240016, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/oduwsdl/ipwb/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 540309618, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/oduwsdl/ipwb/labels/ipwb%20replay', 'name': 'ipwb replay', 'color': 'd4c5f9', 'default': False}]",[],0,"`$ ipwb replay ipwb/samples/indexes/sample-1.cdxj` starts fine reporting 65 mementos from bitchmagazine.org. Accessing one of the URIs in the replay system, however, simply shows ""Error"" in the viewport. The replay python code report the following:
```
looking for org,bitchmagazine)/tag/guns-in-school 20130411210714 in ipwb/samples/indexes/sample-1.cdxj
'locator'
127.0.0.1 - - [31/May/2017 13:13:57] ""GET /20130411210714/bitchmagazine.org/tag/guns-in-school HTTP/1.1"" 500 -
```
This may be due to its creation prior to our usage of the ""locator"" field. In the sample CDXJ files, the ""locator"" is split into two JSON fields, `payload_digest` and `header_digest`. The absence of a locator field causes ipwb replay to return an error.",{},{}
