12626,IssuesEvent,2015-04-21 18:42:53+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,73019,mboersma,6117407,deis,closed,Allow file to be specified for config:push,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/client', 'name': 'client', 'color': 'ff69b4'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/easy-fix', 'name': 'easy-fix', 'color': 'bfe5bf'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],7,"Hey,

It would be good for `deis config:push` to accept a path to a .env file. 

I have 2 apps setup from 1 repo, one for staging and one for production, each have their own .env files.

An example would be: `deis config:push ./env.production`",{},{}
12628,IssuesEvent,2015-07-27 01:46:49+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,73019,mboersma,6117407,deis,closed,"deisctl gets to ""failed/failed"" on a service, and then hangs.","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/deisctl', 'name': 'deisctl', 'color': 'f7c6c7'}]",[],2,"On occasion, if I get a service to exit unexpectedly, then deisctl will hang on any subsequent commands.

Example:

```
$ deisctl stop builder
deis-builder.service: failed/failed
(hangs)
```

With a little bit of debugging code in `fleet/stop.go`, I can see that it's stuck in the for loop there:

```go
		lastSubState = currentState.SystemdSubState
		fmt.Printf(""Waiting for state %s, but in state %s\n"", desiredState, currentState.SystemdSubState) // Added
		time.Sleep(250 * time.Millisecond)
```

Which prints this out every 250 msec:

```
Waiting for state dead, but in state failed
```

I'm not sure if we're legitimately waiting for something to happen, or if `failed` or `dead` should be treated like a special case.",{},{}
