12939,IssuesEvent,2016-03-08 03:16:49+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,334496,ilanschnell,6392739,conda,opened,Remove locking completely,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/conda/conda/labels/Needs%20Decision', 'name': 'Needs Decision', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],0,"I would suggest removing the locking of conda entirely, because it causes more problems, than it solves.  Users just have to be careful not to run multiple instances of conda at once, but even if they do things will work most of the time.  There are only few cases were the file locks are doing a useful job.  Moreover, conda has been designed in a way that most commands can be interrupted and resumed later.  I was never a fan of these locks, because of the additional complexity they added.",{},{}
