13007,IssuesEvent,2016-12-14 14:17:43+00:00,25027539,Clinical-Genomics/scout,405278,moonso,6412433,Clinical-Genomics,closed,ExAC frequency,[],[],1,"Hi!

I have a question about ExAC frequency in Scout. I found a mutation in UNC93B1 (p.Val498Met) in PID132, which was completely fitting the phenotype, rare, coding region and I considered the case solved.
Today I was searching literature to get more info about the mutation. I figured out that the population frequency for ExAC is in Scout 0.005 and on the ExAC website is 0.04, very difference as you can notice. 
Is there some mistake or there another reason for that? 

Thanks!

Best,
Rosa
",{},{}
