13044,IssuesEvent,2016-01-13 23:27:24+00:00,16557526,pysam-developers/pysam,7516054,sbandara,6598771,pysam-developers,opened,C util force_bytes not converting from unicode before Python 3,[],[],0,"Pybedtools 0.7.0 interval names and chromosomes are unicode strings in Python 2. A `TypeError` from pysam's `AlignmentFile.get_tid` can be traced to `force_bytes` in [cutils.pyx](pysam/cutils.pyx) not converting the contig string on Python 2.7.10. The relevant section is:
```python
cdef bytes force_bytes(object s, encoding=""ascii""):
    u""""""convert string or unicode object to bytes, assuming
    ascii encoding.
    """"""
    if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3:
        return s
    elif s is None:
        return None
    elif PyBytes_Check(s):
        return s
    elif PyUnicode_Check(s):
        return s.encode(encoding)
    else:
        raise TypeError(u""Argument must be string, bytes or unicode."")
```
Why do you convert from unicode only when `PY_MAJOR_VERSION` >= 3?",{},{}
