13055,IssuesEvent,2017-01-13 07:10:29+00:00,12024604,OpenCobolIDE/OpenCobolIDE,6699539,GitMensch,6609701,OpenCobolIDE,opened,windows installer: update leads to multiple GnuCOBOL installations in one folder,[],[],0,"Old OCIDE shipped an OpenCOBOL folder (if I remember correctly). Then we had a GnuCOBOL folder with the official 1.1 MinGW package.
The current one is still named GnuCOBOL but contains a slightly patched 2.0rc2.

When installing the first and one of the later versions afterwards there are no problems, but if you installed the second one (which many people did) and install the current one afterwards you end up with the new + some parts of the old one (every file that is not part of the new one).
Despite of the some additional bytes this may lead to confusion (includes the changelogs and manual for both 1.1 and 2.0rc2 for example) and may even lead to weird bugs.

Suggestion: either change the installer to run the uninstallation when doing an update or rename the old GnuCOBOL folder to ""GnuCOBOL_old_$date"" if it exists on installing or change the new folder name to GnuCOBOL-2.0_rc2.",{},{}
