13109,IssuesEvent,2015-06-19 15:21:30+00:00,12235583,elastic/curator,465041,TinLe,6764390,elastic,opened,combining --older-than with --all-indices will cause the timer to not trigger,[],[],0,"This was an accident, but I stumbled onto the bug late last night.  Luckily it was a test server, so deleting all my indices doesn't bother me :-)

I found that using curator to delete indices, if I combined --older-than with -all-indices, there is no timer.  E.g. it starts deleting right away.   This may be working as intended, but I did not know this and have not seen it in the docs.   Also, the --older-than does not work correctly, since I wanted to delete everything older than 30 days.  In this case, the '--all-indices' override and just delete everything.

$ curator --version
curator, version 3.2.0.dev0

# no timer, it just starts deleting immediately
$ curator delete indices --older-than 30 --time-unit days --all-indices --timestring '%Y.%m.%d'
