13624,IssuesEvent,2016-02-01 13:53:57+00:00,17429141,tldr-pages/tldr-python-client,946520,bwh1te,7366472,tldr-pages,closed,Add ability to omit background color option,[],[],3,"Now we can't specify font as dark (or bold, underline, blink, reverse, concealed) without changing background color. Meanwhile we can't specify background color to black (due to termcolor library limitations).

```python
DEFAULT_COLORS = {
    'command': 'red on_grey dark',
    'parameter': 'green dark',
}

In [11]: colors_of('command')
Out[11]: ('red', 'on_grey', ['dark'])  # Correct!

In [12]: colors_of('parameter')
Out[12]: ('green', 'dark', [])  # Not correct!
```

So I think we should to improve `colors_of` method.",{},{}
