13707,IssuesEvent,2017-04-27 17:14:30+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,476301,JamiesHQ,7388996,jupyter,reopened,"Proper way to add ""alert""/""note""/""hint""/""warning""/... boxes?",[],[],12,"I apologize if this has been discussed before, but I didn't find anything about it in the issues ...

I often see colored boxes in Markdown cells, e.g. in `docs/source/examples/Notebook/Notebook Basics.ipynb` (rendered by [Github](https://github.com/jupyter/notebook/blob/master/docs/source/examples/Notebook/Notebook%20Basics.ipynb)/[nbviewer](http://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/jupyter/notebook/blob/master/docs/source/examples/Notebook/Notebook%20Basics.ipynb)).

Those are typically created with raw HTML `<div>`s like this:

``` html
<div class=""alert alert-success"">
Blah blah blah
</div>
```

This looks nice and all, but
1. It's kinda tedious to type
2. The colored boxes (but not their content) get lost in translation to LaTeX

Is there a better way to create those boxes?
",{},{}
13715,IssuesEvent,2016-11-29 17:53:33+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,2482408,michaelpacer,7388996,jupyter,closed,"Documentation uses `sourcecode::` directive, not easily searchable despite being in sphinx docs",[],[],2,"I was looking at [these docs](http://jupyter-notebook.readthedocs.io/en/latest/extending/savehooks.html#examples) in the context of #1928 and noticed that the second example did not display appropriately and the directive was included in the statement. 

After a long rabbit hole, I've been unable to trackdown where and why exactly this was the case, but it may be related to the use of the `sourcecode::` directive, which does not seem to be a part of either sphinx or the standard rst library. 

It may not actually be causing a problem and may instead be that there is also a earlier code-block invocation (previous paragraph ends with ::). But, I wanted to flag this.",{},{}
