14525,IssuesEvent,2015-11-09 23:41:28+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,6504915,bmw,9289019,letsencrypt,closed,Don't set AcceptPathInfo Off in default config,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/apache', 'name': 'apache', 'color': 'fbca04'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/has%20pr', 'name': 'has pr', 'color': '0052cc'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],5,"Hi,

it seems that ``AcceptPathInfo Off`` (https://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/en/mod/core.html#acceptpathinfo) is currently set in the default apache config of Let's encrypt:

https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/74b2e3bc515b5f7e805883a26f1b0e47ed686098/letsencrypt-apache/letsencrypt_apache/options-ssl-apache.conf#L13

This might break web applications like ownCloud which are using routes like seen here: https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/20202

Please consider to remove this config option to avoid having such issues with applications like ownCloud.",{},{}
14532,IssuesEvent,2015-10-08 00:38:59+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,220205,jsha,9289019,letsencrypt,opened,Nginx fails if ssl_session_cache already defined,[],[],0,"Steps to reproduce:

