14616,IssuesEvent,2017-01-27 15:08:57+00:00,56217288,confluentinc/confluent-kafka-python,524990,edenhill,9439498,confluentinc,closed,"AttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'value', Bug?","[{'id': 357948251, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/confluentinc/confluent-kafka-python/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]",[],4,"I am running `AvroConsumer` and it throws the following error:

```
avro-test_1  |   File ""/usr/local/bin/main.py"", line 39, in <module>
avro-test_1  |     msg = consumer.poll(timeout=1.0)
avro-test_1  |   File ""/usr/local/lib/python3.5/dist-packages/confluent_kafka/avro/__init__.py"", line 151, in poll
avro-test_1  |     if not message.value() and not message.key():
