14674,IssuesEvent,2017-11-05 14:05:05+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,1377457,pganssle,9849410,dateutil,opened,"Switch license to Apache 2.0 for all new work, add AUTHORS file","[{'id': 177049977, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}]",[],0,"I think that the Apache 2.0 license has some significant advantages over the BSD license, namely that patents are explicitly dealt with and clause 5 makes it explicit that contributions to the main repo will be licensed under Apache 2.0 *unless otherwise specified*. We still need to keep BSD license around for anyone who has not agreed to relicense, but since Apache and BSD are compatible, it's not a problem for all work going forward to be under the Apache 2.0 license.

As part of this, I think we should also add an `AUTHORS` file, so that the copyright notice is more accurate. I'll compile an `AUTHORS` file and it will be explicit who has their contributions licensed under the old BSD license and who has their contributions licensed under Apache 2.0, and any author on the list can make a PR to add themselves to the Apache 2.0 relicense file. If we get to 100%, we'll drop the old BSD file.",{},{}
14677,IssuesEvent,2018-03-24 17:06:32+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,1377457,pganssle,9849410,dateutil,opened,No documentation for gettz,"[{'id': 177049977, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': 'fef2c0', 'default': False}, {'id': 770220100, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/good%20first%20issue', 'name': 'good first issue', 'color': 'b43dff', 'default': True}, {'id': 149492528, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '159818', 'default': True}, {'id': 177050120, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/time%20zones', 'name': 'time zones', 'color': 'c7def8', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Currently there is no documentation for `gettz`, which is the primary interface through which one gets Olson database zones.

Some prior art that should be cobbled together to make real documentation:

- [Here are some slides about gettz](https://pganssle.github.io/pygotham-2016-dateutil-talk/#/4/3) - [video here](https://youtu.be/X_bCto95Imc?t=20m25s) (audio is messed up)
- [Here is the actual implementation](https://github.com/dateutil/dateutil/blob/master/dateutil/tz/tz.py#L1431)

Unfortunately not a whole lot to go on.",{},{}
