14898,IssuesEvent,2016-12-21 19:54:22+00:00,46293472,Backblaze/B2_Command_Line_Tool,603739,bwbeach,10283486,Backblaze,closed,Detect when local clock differs from B2 clock,[],"[{'login': 'bwbeach', 'id': 603739, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/603739?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/bwbeach', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/bwbeach/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",13,"It would be nice if the command-line tool detected when the clock in the B2 service is too far off from the local clock.  This matters when setting `src_last_modified_millis` in a file upload.  

What should happen when the clocks don't match?  Is printing a warning enough?  Should sync stop?",{},{}
