14997,IssuesEvent,2018-05-22 18:59:23+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,5420744,TobyRoseman,10639145,apple,opened,recommend_from_interactions fails for new user,[],[],0,"The following code:
```python
import turicreate as tc

data = tc.SFrame({'user_id': [""Ann"", ""Ann"", ""Ann"", ""Brian"", ""Brian"", ""Brian""],
                          'item_id': [""Item1"", ""Item2"", ""Item4"", ""Item2"", ""Item3"", ""Item5""],
                          'rating': [1, 3, 2, 5, 4, 2]})
model = tc.item_similarity_recommender.create(data, target='rating', verbose=False)

empty_sframe = tc.SFrame({'user_id': [], 'item_id': []})
model.recommend_from_interactions(empty_sframe)
```
produces: `IndexError: SArray index out of range`.

At the very least, the length of the input should be checked and if zero a helpful error message should be given. However I think we can do better than that, perhaps just return the most popular items.",{},{}
15013,IssuesEvent,2018-06-14 19:49:44+00:00,11001295,nexB/aboutcode-toolkit,4853767,mjherzog,10789967,nexB,opened,Summarize package-level data in Attribution Notice,"[{'id': 45346491, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NTM0NjQ5MQ==', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nexB/aboutcode-toolkit/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 965108848, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw5NjUxMDg4NDg=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nexB/aboutcode-toolkit/labels/needs%20design', 'name': 'needs design', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'DennisClark', 'id': 4991620, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjQ5OTE2MjA=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/4991620?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/DennisClark', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/DennisClark/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"When an Inventory data file is based on Package-level information, there are many cases where generating an Attribution entry for each Package may increase the length of the Attribution Notice significantly with redundant information. The most prominent use cases are likely Java projects/Components like Apache Batik or Spring Framework where you many have 10 or more JAR packages with same copyright and license information. We should offer some way to summarize this type of data by project/Component for Attribution Notices. This clearly needs discussion and design.",{},{}
15014,IssuesEvent,2018-04-02 02:26:45+00:00,11001295,nexB/aboutcode-toolkit,4246379,chinyeungli,10789967,nexB,closed,Define how we are packaging ABOUT,"[{'id': 46448915, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nexB/aboutcode-toolkit/labels/requirement', 'name': 'requirement', 'color': 'eb6420', 'default': False}]",[],2,"For now a simple .py script is best. 
Later we need to have extra libs and the single file approach will no longer work. 
