15215,IssuesEvent,2017-11-21 15:16:26+00:00,18302786,IDSIA/sacred,1595030,lucasdavid,11296960,IDSIA,closed,Keras progress bar doesn't look right since keras update,[],[],1,"Since Keras has updated, adding `ex.captured_out_filter = apply_backspaces_and_linefeeds` no longer helps sacred to override the repeated lines with FileObserver, making the logs extremely long. This effect also happens in the terminal from which the script was called.

An [issue](https://github.com/fchollet/keras/issues/8414) has been opened at keras repository, but a contributor suggests this is a sacred problem.

**Steps to reproduce**

`progbar_test.py`:
```python
import keras
from keras import callbacks
from keras.datasets import mnist
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sacred import Experiment

ex = Experiment('training-a-keras-model')

@ex.config
def my_config():
    batch_size = 128
    num_classes = 10
    epochs = 20

@ex.automain
def main(batch_size, num_classes, epoch):
    (x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
    x_train = x_train.reshape(60000, 784).astype('float32') / 255
    x_test = x_test.reshape(10000, 784).astype('float32') / 255
    y_train = keras.utils.to_categorical(y_train, num_classes)
    y_test = keras.utils.to_categorical(y_test, num_classes)

    model = Sequential([
      Dense(1024, activation='relu', name='fc1', input_dim=784),
      Dense(1024, activation='relu', name='fc3'),
      Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax', name='predictions')
    ])
    model.compile(optimizer='adam',
                  loss='categorical_crossentropy',
                  metrics=['accuracy'])

    history = model.fit(x_train, y_train,
                        batch_size=batch_size,
                        epochs=epochs,
                        verbose=1,
                        validation_data=(x_test, y_test))
```
```shell
(tf) $ python test.py -F ./test/
Using TensorFlow backend.
INFO - training-a-keras-model - Running command 'main'
INFO - training-a-keras-model - Started run with ID ""3""
Train on 60000 samples, validate on 10000 samples
Epoch 1/20

  128/60000 [..............................] - ETA: 1:22 - loss: 2.3237 - acc: 0.0781
