15368,IssuesEvent,2018-05-25 18:04:26+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,3085284,NikolajBjorner,11668813,Z3Prover,closed,Sort mismatch at argument #1 for function (declare-fun = (Real Real) Bool),[],"[{'login': 'kenmcmil', 'id': 8010069, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/8010069?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/kenmcmil', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kenmcmil/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"When running z3 build at commit fefd00aa4980dd7410f2315a6e3033c349f6b266 on the input file shown below, I get the error message:

```
(error ""query failed: Sort mismatch at argument #1 for function (declare-fun = (Real Real) Bool) supplied sort is Int"")
```

Judging by the error messages I received for other input files it seems like `duality` doesn’t support mixing reals and integers, so this is probably just a confusing error message rather than an actual bug. This example doesn’t use `=` anywhere. (I removed everything possible from the example so it’s pretty meaningless at this point).

``` smt
(set-logic HORN)
(set-option :fixedpoint.engine duality)
(set-option :int-real-coercions false)
(declare-var HEAP (Array Int Int))
(declare-var a Int)
(declare-var i Int)
(declare-var n Int)
(declare-var s Real)
(declare-rel QUERY ())
(declare-rel Inv (Int Int Int Real (Array Int Int)))
(rule
 (=> (not (<= n 0))
     (Inv 0 a n 0.0 HEAP)))
(rule
 (=> (and (Inv i a n s HEAP) (>= i n))
     QUERY))
(rule
 (=> (Inv i a n s HEAP)
     (Inv i a n (/ (to_real (select HEAP a)) (to_real n)) HEAP)))
(query QUERY)
```
",{},{}
15370,IssuesEvent,2018-05-14 20:11:42+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,6924766,HalleyYoung,11668813,Z3Prover,opened,Any way to retrieve mapping from bit-blasted CNF formula back to BitVector variables?,[],[],0,"I have used z3 in several cases, and find it very useful.  However, I am currently dealing with a problem where I need a fairly random distribution of satisfying assignments for a given BitVector problem.  This is exactly what the tool weightgen (https://bitbucket.org/kuldeepmeel/weightgen) does with CNF formulas.  Is there any way to extract a bit-blasted CNF formula from Z3, solve it using another solver (in this case weightgen), and plug the satisfying assignment back in to retrieve the solutions to the original problem?",{},{}
