15472,IssuesEvent,2018-01-10 20:19:36+00:00,99273369,NeurodataWithoutBorders/pynwb,15089451,NileGraddis,12140348,NeurodataWithoutBorders,opened,Directly assessing integration test coverage,[],[],0,"Currently, the scheme for reporting integration test coverage (i.e. which containers were run) relies on a decorator applied to the test case, which registers the tested class into a global variable. This variable is inspected by test.py and used to generate a report of the containers which are missing integration tests.

This scheme does not have a way to distinguish complete from incomplete test cases and also relies on the decorator being up-to-date with the test case's code.

To see this issue, simply run:
`python test.py -iv`

- [x] Have you ensured the feature or change was not already [reported](https://github.com/NeurodataWithoutBorders/pynwb/issues/) ?
- [x] Have you included a brief and descriptive title?
- [x] Have you included a clear description of the problem you are trying to solve?
- [x] Have you included a minimal code snippet that reproduces the issue you are encountering?
",{},{}
