15672,IssuesEvent,2016-04-22 07:13:56+00:00,36042880,python-bugzilla/python-bugzilla,493157,mprpic,12552361,python-bugzilla,closed,KeyError when querying bug data from Bugzilla version 3.x,[],[],4,"I'm trying to get bug information from several Bugzilla instances, namely:

    In [12]: for url in urls:
       ....:        bz = Bugzilla(url)
       ....:        print(url, bz.bz_ver_major, bz.bz_ver_minor)
       ....: 
    ('https://bugzilla.novell.com', 3, 4)
    ('https://bugs.gentoo.org', 3, 0)
    ('https://bugs.mageia.org', 4, 4)
    ('https://bugzilla.redhat.com', 4, 4)

When trying `bz.getbug(123)` on Novell's and Gentoo's Bugzilla instance, I hit the else branch of [this](https://github.com/python-bugzilla/python-bugzilla/blob/0b2397db551b8969fa7b71a15cf2ff80d3146437/bugzilla/base.py#L1032) check that tries to access `b['internals']`. This attribute does not exist in the bug dictionary so it fails with a `KeyError: 'internals'` traceback.

If I remove that check for the BZ version altogether, all seems to work just fine. Was the `internals` used at some point and has been removed now? I'd submit a patch removing that check but would like to see first if it's actually used for anything. I can't seem to find any `internals` attribute exposed by any Bugzilla instances.

Thanks!
",{},{}
15673,IssuesEvent,2018-01-04 10:49:50+00:00,47192570,AfricasTalkingLtd/africastalking-python,1404985,ianjuma,12639968,AfricasTalkingLtd,closed,[BUG]: `getUserData` method is broken.,[],[],1,"The [`getUserData` method](https://github.com/AfricasTalkingLtd/africastalking-python/blob/master/africastalking/AfricasTalkingGateway.py#L274) always returns `AfricasTalkingGatewayException`.

On further probing, it turns out the method makes a `POST` requests instead of a `GET` request to the api endpoint. This is because of how the [sendRequest](https://github.com/AfricasTalkingLtd/africastalking-python/blob/master/africastalking/AfricasTalkingGateway.py#L283) method is implemented.

How to reproduce:

```python
url = 'https://api.africastalking.com/version1/user?username=your-username'
headers = { 'Accept' : 'application/json',  'apikey' : XXXX}
r = requests.post(url, headers)
print(r.status_code) # status code: 405
print(r.test) # text: HTTP method not allowed, supported methods: GET
```
I apologize I have used `requests` to reproduce the error instead of the `AfricasTalkingGateway` class. This because the error gets masked by the `AfricasTalkingGatewayException` I'm using requests to simulate [this line](https://github.com/AfricasTalkingLtd/africastalking-python/blob/master/africastalking/AfricasTalkingGateway.py#L289) in `sendRequest`.

Changing the http method from `POST` to `GET` fixes this:
```python
url = 'https://api.africastalking.com/version1/user?username=your-username'
headers = { 'Accept' : 'application/json',  'apikey' : XXXX}
r = requests.get(url, headers)
print(r.status_code) # status code: 200
print(r.test) # text:{'UserData': {'balance': 'KES XXX'}}
```





",{},{}
