15875,IssuesEvent,2016-04-08 14:26:08+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,13677368,drmarkwslater,13271048,ganga-devs,closed,Tasks integration test,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ganga-devs/ganga/labels/Core', 'name': 'Core', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}]",[],1,"Hi all,

I'm just adding a small issue to ask if we can make a small set of integration tests to check the expected behavior of the tasks system as part of 6.1.19.

I keep getting confused with the tasks as it's not something I've a lot of experience with and I somehow feel a simple test which constructs a simple task which fires off a simple job and finishes would be useful to demonstrate the expected behavior.

Nothing too complex but maybe a simple task with a simple transform would also be extremely helpful for reference/education.

Thanks,

Rob",{},{}
