### Issue Description
Just now, I installed the SDK from the Installer. Directly after installation, I wasn't able to load the module from Python with the following error message: `ImportError: DLL load failed: Das angegebene Modul wurde nicht gefunden.`. I tracked this down to be a VC++ 2017 Redistributable problem probably. I installed the amd64 package of those, restarted my machine and it worked flawless.

Now I'm not sure if this issue would have persisted without the manual installation of the VC++ 2017 Redistributables. Does the SDK installer ship these? If yes, you should probably suggest a restart after installation as well. Though the Viewer worked without a restart, the Python library did not. I did build the library before on my main machine (now using a temporary replacement due to hardware failure on my main machine, that's why Im using the pre-copiled binaries). Those worked out-of-the-box probably due to the necessary runtime librares already being available on the machine.
",{},{}
