16376,IssuesEvent,2018-06-22 06:47:00+00:00,85208106,src-d/wmd-relax,2793551,vmarkovtsev,15128793,src-d,closed,TailVocabularyOptimizer will mistakenly discard all words when tail size is 0,[],[],1,"when the bag of words is too big and trigger VocabularyOptimizer, if ```tail_size``` is 0, then the whole bow will be discarded by mistake.
```wmd-relax/wmd/__init__.py``` line 92-93
it is
```
weights = weights[:-tail_size][:vocabulary_max]
words = words[sorter[:-tail_size]][:vocabulary_max]
```
And it should be 
```
weights = weights[:len(weights)-tail_size][:vocabulary_max]
words = words[sorter[:len(words)-tail_size]][:vocabulary_max]
```",{},{}
