16501,IssuesEvent,2017-08-31 13:28:08+00:00,55233339,glomex/gcdt,33456,markfink,15928082,glomex,opened,[ramuda] migrate the depreated old wiring events configuration into new format,"[{'id': 351113231, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/glomex/gcdt/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],0,"The two events implementations in ramuda (one uses a list for config, the other a dictionary) prevent us from using config validation for the `events` section.

In order to phase out the old deprecated events implementation (>700 lines of code) we propose the following approach:

* migrate an old configuration into the new format
* print out the new config format as a log.warn
* use the new events implementation
* remove the old deprecated events wiring implementation with gcdt 0.3.x 
* activate config validation for events (just comment out the relevant section in openapi_ramuda.yaml)
",{},{}
