16937,IssuesEvent,2017-10-23 23:34:10+00:00,94455745,dask/dask-ml,1276576,gpfreitas,17131925,dask,opened,@wraps breaks introspection,[],[],0,"https://github.com/dask/dask-ml/blob/cb3d0ea392a277cade35405f6b156f22a1616551/dask_ml/datasets.py#L11

The use of `@wraps` here leads to wrong behavior of some introspection tools, like `??` in Jupyter (will show you the code for the sklearn version).

I feel that it's best to wrap thing manually (assigning the `__name__`, `__doc__` and `__module__` attributes for `inner` manually), after line 17, before the `return`.

This issue is making some unpleasant workarounds necessary in the `xarray_filters` codebase (same `datasets.py` file) (where we are trying to give more helpful docstrings users beyond what's in sklearn).",{},{}
