17483,IssuesEvent,2017-09-13 17:15:29+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,[global] section for cells without %run?,"[{'id': 325435541, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SoS/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': False}]",[],1,"With #805 , currently global sections defined in a notebook will be prepeneded to workflow executed by the `%run` magic so that we do not have to define them again and again for each cell.

However, the cells containing `[global]` sections are not executed without `%run` so the following would fail with `a` not defined.

```
---
[global]
a=1
---
print(a)
---
```

We can argue that `[global]` is a workflow cell and `print(a)` is in a SoS (scratch) cell so they do not work with each other, but perhaps it is better for us to 

1. Visually differentiate two types of cells... or
2. Make `[global]` truly global also to SoS cells
",{},{}
17485,IssuesEvent,2017-08-20 00:16:47+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,opened,%from magic import class / function definitions from other sos scripts or SoS Notebooks,[],[],0,"SoS is a great book-keeping tool, but I still find myself relying on utility scripts for pure Python code (imported in SoS as `from .utils import ...`). Is it reasonable request to import from other SoS scripts functions and classes defined, as is? I can immediately see myself using a `utils.ipynb` to keep all my utility functions, nicely separated into sections, subsection, etc, documented with markdown cells here and there, tested with scratch pad and %preview, rendered to nice HTML for review, and above all be able to load to all other SoS scripts and notebooks. Currently we have 

```
%from utils include some_step
```

and hopefully we can also have 

```
%from utils import some_functions, some_classes
```
",{},{}
