17680,IssuesEvent,2017-02-17 15:01:09+00:00,66776276,python-social-auth/social-core,7237250,NBajanca,21279195,python-social-auth,opened,race condition on access_token_expired(),[],[],0,"[access_token_expired](https://github.com/python-social-auth/social-core/blob/9fb7a06a0618aa88d62b980392f77b5a5f91f98f/social_core/storage.py#L94) has the following logic:

    def access_token_expired(self):
        expiration = self.expiration_timedelta()
        return expiration and expiration.total_seconds() <= 0

Why not: 

    class UserMixin(object):
        ...
        RACE_CONDITION_TIMEOUT = 2
        ...
        def access_token_expired(self):
            expiration = self.expiration_timedelta()
            return expiration and expiration.total_seconds() <= RACE_CONDITION_TIMEOUT

The strategies could override this value (thinking, for example, in creating a settings option for Django)
",{},{}
