grpcio-tools (1.8.4)
jaeger-client (3.7.2.dev0, /src/jaeger-client) [current master]
```
Python version
```
python --version
Python 3.6.3
```

I'm using this as a test zipkin backend
```
gcr.io/stackdriver-trace-docker/zipkin-collector
```
Thanks for your help.",{},{}
18194,IssuesEvent,2018-08-16 02:13:36+00:00,71948498,localstack/localstack,1794527,ccorcos,28732122,localstack,opened,Persist DynamoDb Streams,[],[],0,"Localstack persists the DynamoDb data, but does not persist the streams configuration. 

The stream configuration is set up when you create or update a table. However, the table info is persisted so the table is already created. Thus you're stuck in an awkward position.

https://github.com/localstack/localstack/issues/519

Temporary workaround is to disable streams and reenable stream every time localstack boots up. Not ideal.

Another idea is just to iterate through the existing DynamoDb tables and set up any streams. That might be easier to implement.

Thanks,

Chet",{},{}
