18560,IssuesEvent,2012-02-20 08:33:55+00:00,3342046,RDFLib/rdflib,16417,gjhiggins,1401847,RDFLib,closed,broken link in pypi for rdflib 3.1.0,[],[],0,"jaakko.t...@gmail.com, 2011-03-22T13:19:15.000Z
<pre>
<b>What steps will reproduce the problem?</b>
1. easy_install rdflib -U

<b>What is the expected output? What do you see instead?</b>

Expected that easy install will retrieve and install RDFLib:

Instead got:

install_dir C:\Python26\Lib\site-packages\
Searching for rdflib
Reading http://pypi.python.org/simple/rdflib/
Reading http://rdflib.net/
Best match: rdflib 3.1.0
Downloading http://rdflib.net/rdflib-3.1.0.tar.gz
error: Can't download http://rdflib.net/rdflib-3.1.0.tar.gz: 404 Not Found

Comment 1 by jaakko.t...@gmail.com
By the way: is there a reason you haven't submitted the package directly to pypi, but instead rely on a third-party hosted server? (rdflib.net)

We are building an application on top of rdflib + surf and it is crucial important for us to be able to rely on easy_install for processing the dependencies.


Comment 2 by gromgull
This was my bad - we previously used only rdflib.net, but are slowly moving things to google code (here) and pypi. 

I've changed the download link in pypi, it now appears to work for me (but it also did work when I made the release). Can you please confirm that it's ok for you? 

Cheers,


Comment 3 by jaakko.t...@gmail.com
I can confirm that install from pypi now works!

Also thank you for creating updated 3.1.0 version!


Comment 4 by jaakko.t...@gmail.com
Also, I'm sorry to spam you with this, but link to the license is also broken in pypi: http://www.rdflib.net/latest/LICENSE

This obviously isn't such a big issue since the LICENSE is already available inside the package.


Comment 5 by gromgull
Fixed! Thanks for the bug report!
</pre>",{},{}
